{{Infobox figure skater |name= Geoffry Varner |image= Geoffryvarner.jpg |caption= |country= [[United States]] |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1987|3|2}} |residence= |height= |coach= [[Barbara Roles-Williams]] |choreographer= [[Marina Zoueva]], [[Irina Romanova (figure skater)|Irina Romanova]] |skating club= Peninsula Skating Club |retired= |combined total= 170.48 |combined date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix|2005 JGP Croatia]] |SP score= 57.82 |SP date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix|2005 JGP Croatia]] |FS score= 112.66 |FS date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix|2005 JGP Croatia]] }} '''Geoffry Varner''' (born March 2, 1987 in [[Palo Alto, California]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He was the 2006 U.S. Junior bronze medalist and placed third at the Junior Grand Prix final in 2005. In his first year as a senior, he has been given two senior Grand Prix assignments.
In his first senior Grand Prix appearance at Skate Canada, Varner placed 11th.
Geoffry has two older brothers. Jeremy is a professional baseball player for the Chicago Cubs farm system.
